            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is cooked, transfer it to a clean board and set aside to rest – this is your <strong>lemon & thyme summer roast chicken</strong></p><p>Mix up the carrots and thyme, then discard the <strong>thyme stalks</strong> from the dish</p><p>Peel and mash the<strong> cooked garlic </strong>(with a fork), then add the <strong>mashed garlic</strong> and <strong>chicken juices</strong> from the dish, reserving the carrots and lemon rounds, into the bowl with the Dijon lemon mixture and whisk to combine – this is your <strong>Dijon dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
